Human‑Behaviour Browser Action Policy
All browser interactions must mimic realistic human behaviour.
Every action—navigation, clicking, scrolling, filling forms, extracting content, or executing scripts—must follow these constraints:

1. Timing & Pace
Insert natural, non‑uniform delays between actions.

Avoid machine‑perfect timing (e.g., no constant 0.2s intervals).

Use human‑like ranges such as:

Short pauses: 300–900ms

Thinking pauses: 1.2–3.5s

Occasional long pauses: 4–8s

2. Mouse Behaviour
Mouse movements must be:

Curved, not linear

Variable in speed

With slight overshoot or micro‑corrections

No teleporting the cursor directly onto elements.

3. Scrolling Behaviour
Scroll in small increments, not full jumps.

Use momentum‑based scrolling (accelerate → glide → decelerate).

Occasionally scroll past the target and adjust back up.

4. Navigation Behaviour
Do not instantly interact after page load.

Wait for visible content to settle.

Occasionally hover over elements before clicking.

5. Form Interaction
Typing must be:

Character‑by‑character

With variable speed

With occasional micro‑pauses

Optional: introduce rare backspaces to simulate correction.

6. Page Exploration
When using actions like:

/browse_and_extract

/get_html_source

/extract_all_links

/get_page_info

/monitor_network_requests

…ensure the agent:

Scrolls through the page before extracting

Pauses to “read” sections

Interacts only with visible elements

Avoids rapid-fire requests

7. Click & Hover Actions
For:

/click

/hover_element

/press_key

/wait_for_element

…apply:

Hover before clicking

Slight movement jitter

Occasional hesitation before action

8. Screenshot Behaviour
For /screenshot:

Take screenshots only after a natural viewing delay

Optionally scroll slightly before capturing

Avoid capturing instantly after navigation

9. JavaScript Execution
For /execute_js:

Only run JS that a human could plausibly trigger indirectly

Avoid rapid repeated JS calls

Avoid full‑page DOM dumps unless preceded by human‑like exploration

10. Network & Console Monitoring
For:

/monitor_network_requests

/get_console_logs

…simulate:

Staying on the page for the duration

Occasional scrolls or hovers during monitoring

1. Install the python client (docs) if you don't already have it installed.

copy
$ pip install gradio_client
2. Find the API endpoint below corresponding to your desired function in the app. Copy the code snippet, replacing the placeholder values with your own input data. If this is a private Space, you may need to pass your Hugging Face token as well (read more). Or use the 
API Recorder

 to automatically generate your API requests.

API name: /browse_and_extract Browse URL and extract text from selector
copy
from gradio_client import Client

client = Client("diamond-in/Browser-Use-mcp")
result = client.predict(
	url="https://example.com",
	selector="body",
	use_persistent=False,
	api_name="/browse_and_extract"
)
print(result)
Accepts 3 parameters:
url str Default: "https://example.com"

The input value that is provided in the "URL" Textbox component.

selector str Default: "body"

The input value that is provided in the "CSS Selector" Textbox component.

use_persistent bool Default: False

The input value that is provided in the "Use Persistent Browser" Checkbox component.

Returns 1 element
str

The output value that appears in the "Extracted Text" Textbox component.

API name: /screenshot Take screenshot of URL
