API name: /make_http_request Make HTTP request with custom method, headers, and data (like Postman)
copy
from gradio_client import Client

client = Client("diamond-in/Browser-Use-mcp")
result = client.predict(
	url="https://api.example.com/data",
	method="GET",
	headers="{
  "Content-Type": "application/json",
  "User-Agent": "MCP-Browser/1.0"
}",
	data="{
  "key": "value"
}",
	use_persistent=False,
	api_name="/make_http_request"
)
print(result)
Accepts 5 parameters:
url str Default: "https://api.example.com/data"

The input value that is provided in the "URL" Textbox component.

method Literal['GET', 'POST', 'PUT', 'PATCH', 'DELETE', 'HEAD', 'OPTIONS'] Default: "GET"

The input value that is provided in the "Method" Dropdown component.

headers str Default: "{ "Content-Type": "application/json", "User-Agent": "MCP-Browser/1.0" }"

The input value that is provided in the "Headers (JSON or key:value format)" Code component.

data str Default: "{ "key": "value" }"

The input value that is provided in the "Body Data (for POST/PUT/PATCH)" Code component.

use_persistent bool Default: False

The input value that is provided in the "Use Persistent Browser" Checkbox component.

Returns 1 element
str

The output value that appears in the "Response" Code component.

